minGasLimit.d: Minimum the gas limit may ever be

gasLimitBoundDivisor.d: The bound divisor of the gas limit, used in update calculations

maxRefundQuotient.d: Maximum refund quotient; max tx refund is min(tx.gasUsed/maxRefundQuotient, tx.gasRefund)

initialBaseFee.d: Initial base fee on first EIP1559 block

blobGasPerBlob.d: The base fee for blob gas per blob

targetBlobGasPerBlock.d: The target blob gas consumed per block

maxblobGasPerBlock.d: The max blob gas allowable per block

blobGasPriceUpdateFraction.d: The denominator used in the exponential when calculating a blob gas price

base.d: Gas base cost, used e.g. for ChainID opcode (Istanbul)

exp.d: Base fee of the EXP opcode

expByte.d: Times ceil(log256(exponent)) for the EXP instruction

keccak256.d: Base fee of the SHA3 opcode

keccak256Word.d: Once per word of the SHA3 operation's data

sload.d: Base fee of the SLOAD opcode

sstoreSet.d: Once per SSTORE operation if the zeroness changes from zero

sstoreReset.d: Once per SSTORE operation if the zeroness does not change from zero

sstoreRefund.d: Once per SSTORE operation if the zeroness changes to zero

jumpdest.d: Base fee of the JUMPDEST opcode

log.d: Base fee of the LOG opcode

logData.d: Per byte in a LOG* operation's data

logTopic.d: Multiplied by the * of the LOG*, per LOG transaction. e.g. LOG0 incurs 0 * c_txLogTopicGas, LOG4 incurs 4 * c_txLogTopicGas

create.d: Base fee of the CREATE opcode

call.d: Base fee of the CALL opcode

callStipend.d: Free gas given at beginning of call

callValueTransfer.d: Paid for CALL when the value transfor is non-zero

callNewAccount.d: Paid for CALL when the destination address didn't exist prior

memory.d: Times the address of the (highest referenced byte in memory + 1). NOTE: referencing happens on read, write and in instructions such as RETURN and CALL

quadCoeffDiv.d: Divisor for the quadratic particle of the memory cost equation

tx.d: Per transaction. NOTE: Not payable on data of calls between transactions

txCreation.d: The cost of creating a contract via tx

txDataZero.d: Per byte of data attached to a transaction that equals zero. NOTE: Not payable on data of calls between transactions

txDataNonZero.d: Per byte of data attached to a transaction that is not equal to zero. NOTE: Not payable on data of calls between transactions

copy.d: Multiplied by the number of 32-byte words that are copied (round up) for any *COPY operation and added

stop.d: Base fee of the STOP opcode

add.d: Base fee of the ADD opcode

mul.d: Base fee of the MUL opcode

sub.d: Base fee of the SUB opcode

div.d: Base fee of the DIV opcode

sdiv.d: Base fee of the SDIV opcode

mod.d: Base fee of the MOD opcode

smod.d: Base fee of the SMOD opcode

addmod.d: Base fee of the ADDMOD opcode

mulmod.d: Base fee of the MULMOD opcode

signextend.d: Base fee of the SIGNEXTEND opcode

lt.d: Base fee of the LT opcode

gt.d: Base fee of the GT opcode

slt.d: Base fee of the SLT opcode

sgt.d: Base fee of the SGT opcode

eq.d: Base fee of the EQ opcode

iszero.d: Base fee of the ISZERO opcode

and.d: Base fee of the AND opcode

or.d: Base fee of the OR opcode

xor.d: Base fee of the XOR opcode

not.d: Base fee of the NOT opcode

byte.d: Base fee of the BYTE opcode

address.d: Base fee of the ADDRESS opcode

balance.d: Base fee of the BALANCE opcode

origin.d: Base fee of the ORIGIN opcode

caller.d: Base fee of the CALLER opcode

callvalue.d: Base fee of the CALLVALUE opcode

calldataload.d: Base fee of the CALLDATALOAD opcode

calldatasize.d: Base fee of the CALLDATASIZE opcode

calldatacopy.d: Base fee of the CALLDATACOPY opcode

codesize.d: Base fee of the CODESIZE opcode

codecopy.d: Base fee of the CODECOPY opcode

gasprice.d: Base fee of the GASPRICE opcode

extcodesize.d: Base fee of the EXTCODESIZE opcode

extcodecopy.d: Base fee of the EXTCODECOPY opcode

blockhash.d: Base fee of the BLOCKHASH opcode

coinbase.d: Base fee of the COINBASE opcode

timestamp.d: Base fee of the TIMESTAMP opcode

number.d: Base fee of the NUMBER opcode

difficulty.d: Base fee of the DIFFICULTY opcode

gaslimit.d: Base fee of the GASLIMIT opcode

pop.d: Base fee of the POP opcode

mload.d: Base fee of the MLOAD opcode

mstore.d: Base fee of the MSTORE opcode

mstore8.d: Base fee of the MSTORE8 opcode

sstore.d: Base fee of the SSTORE opcode

jump.d: Base fee of the JUMP opcode

jumpi.d: Base fee of the JUMPI opcode

pc.d: Base fee of the PC opcode

msize.d: Base fee of the MSIZE opcode

gas.d: Base fee of the GAS opcode

push.d: Base fee of the PUSH opcode

dup.d: Base fee of the DUP opcode

swap.d: Base fee of the SWAP opcode

callcode.d: Base fee of the CALLCODE opcode

return.d: Base fee of the RETURN opcode

invalid.d: Base fee of the INVALID opcode

selfdestruct.d: Base fee of the SELFDESTRUCT opcode

delegatecall.d: Base fee of the DELEGATECALL opcode

modexpGquaddivisor.d: Gquaddivisor from modexp precompile for gas calculation

ecAdd.d: Gas costs for curve addition precompile

ecMul.d: Gas costs for curve multiplication precompile

ecPairing.d: Base gas costs for curve pairing precompile

ecPairingWord.d: Gas costs regarding curve pairing precompile input length

revert.d: Base fee of the REVERT opcode

staticcall.d: Base fee of the STATICCALL opcode

returndatasize.d: Base fee of the RETURNDATASIZE opcode

returndatacopy.d: Base fee of the RETURNDATACOPY opcode

shl.d: Base fee of the SHL opcode

shr.d: Base fee of the SHR opcode

sar.d: Base fee of the SAR opcode

extcodehash.d: Base fee of the EXTCODEHASH opcode

create2.d: Base fee of the CREATE2 opcode

blake2Round.d: Gas cost per round for the Blake2 F precompile

sstoreSentryGasEIP2200.d: Minimum gas required to be present for an SSTORE call, not consumed

sstoreNoopGasEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation if the value doesn't change

sstoreDirtyGasEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation if a dirty value is changed

sstoreInitGasEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation from clean zero to non-zero

sstoreInitRefundEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation for resetting to the original zero value

sstoreCleanGasEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation from clean non-zero to something else

sstoreCleanRefundEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation for resetting to the original non-zero value

sstoreClearRefundEIP2200.d: Once per SSTORE operation for clearing an originally existing storage slot

chainid.d: Base fee of the CHAINID opcode

selfbalance.d: Base fee of the SELFBALANCE opcode

coldsload.d: Gas cost of the first read of storage from a given location (per transaction)

coldaccountaccess.d: Gas cost of the first read of a given address (per transaction)

warmstorageread.d: Gas cost of reading storage locations which have already loaded 'cold'

accessListStorageKeyCost.d: Gas cost per storage key in an Access List transaction

accessListAddressCost.d: Gas cost per storage key in an Access List transaction

basefee.d: Gas cost of the BASEFEE opcode

prevrandao.d: Base fee of the PREVRANDAO opcode (previously DIFFICULTY)

push0.d: Base fee of the PUSH0 opcode

initCodeWordCost.d: Gas to pay for each word (32 bytes) of initcode when creating a contract

tstore.d: Base fee of the TSTORE opcode

tload.d: Base fee of the TLOAD opcode

simpleGasPerBlob.d: The basic gas fee for each blob

minBlobGasPrice.d: The minimum fee per blob gas

kzgPointEvaluationGasPrecompilePrice.d: The fee associated with the point evaluation precompile

blobhash.d: Base fee of the BLOBHASH opcode

mcopy.d: Base fee of the MCOPY opcode

blobbasefee.d: Gas cost of the BLOBBASEFEE opcode

minimumDifficulty.d: The minimum that the difficulty may ever be

difficultyBoundDivisor.d: The bound divisor of the difficulty, used in the update calculations

durationLimit.d: The decision boundary on the blocktime duration used to determine whether difficulty should go up or not

minerReward.d: The amount a miner gets rewarded for mining a block

difficultyBombDelay.d: the amount of blocks to delay the difficulty bomb with

blobCommitmentVersionKzg.d: The number indicated a versioned hash is a KZG commitment

fieldElementsPerBlob.d: The number of field elements allowed per blob

stackLimit.d: Maximum size of VM stack allowed

maxExtraDataSize.d: Maximum size extra data may be after Genesis

maxInitCodeSize.d: Maximum length of initialization code when creating a contract

historicalRootsLength.d: The modulo parameter of the beaconroot ring buffer in the beaconroot statefull precompile
